&lt;p&gt;Specialist Health Adviser Band 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint an individual who is hardworking, motivated and energetic to join a well-established health advising team in a busy sexual health, contraception and HIV department. The specialist health adviser role has responsibility for managing the care of women who have HIV, Hepatitis B or Syphilis in pregnancy. The post also has responsibility to offer specialist advice and on-going care for women living with HIV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be a referral point for all women who have declined blood borne virus screening (BBV) in pregnancy and will have responsibility for the follow up, discussion of testing and onward referral for this group where appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will also be responsible for delivering a monthly educational session to midwives on the management of HIV and other BBV during pregnancy, and be a specialist adviser within BSUH.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must be an NMC registered nurse or midwife&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your hard work and commitment will be rewarded by relevant training, and opportunities to further develop specific areas of interest.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a 22.5 hour post and may include working some Saturdays (on a rotational basis) and some evening clinics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Afra Barrett&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Senior Health Adviser&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address afra.barrett1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number01273 664716&lt;/p&gt;
